Confirmed. `AddIdentityAndAttachments` doesn't touch `ExecutionResults`, so after a DB wipe the table only has its original 6 columns. The `--no-build` flag I put in `server-init.sh` made `dotnet ef` fail (no compiled binaries in the mounted source dir), so `AddExecutionResultColumns` never ran. Your app restarted against a DB missing `Verdict`, `SubmissionId`, `TestCaseId`, `WallTimeMs`, `PeakMemoryKb` on `ExecutionResults`. Any `.Include(s => s.ExecutionResult)` explodes. Orgs never touches that table, so it works.

Two things: fix the script, and recover the server right now.

**Immediate server fix** — run this on the server (no wipe needed, just adds the missing columns):

```bash
source /opt/webide/.env
docker compose exec postgres psql -U webide -d webide -c '
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "PeakMemoryKb" integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "SubmissionId"  integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "TestCaseId"   integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "Verdict"      integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "WallTimeMs"   integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS "IX_ExecutionResults_TestCaseId" ON "ExecutionResults" ("TestCaseId");
  INSERT INTO "__EFMigrationsHistory" VALUES ('"'"'20260611000000_AddExecutionResultColumns'"'"', '"'"'9.0.16'"'"') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
'
docker compose restart webide-app webide-worker
```

Now fix the script so it never has this problem again:

Three commands, in order:

**1. Pull the latest code**
```bash
git -C /opt/webide pull origin server-fixes
```

**2. Add the missing columns (no wipe needed)**
```bash
source /opt/webide/.env && \
docker compose -f /opt/webide/docker-compose.yml exec postgres psql -U webide -d webide -c '
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "PeakMemoryKb" integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "SubmissionId"  integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "TestCaseId"   integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "Verdict"      integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  ALTER TABLE "ExecutionResults" ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "WallTimeMs"   integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
  CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS "IX_ExecutionResults_TestCaseId" ON "ExecutionResults" ("TestCaseId");
